reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: To contribute towards reducing the malaria burden to pre-elimination levels and bringing malaria-related mortality to zero by 2020.

description.narrative: Nigeria - Malaria - Catholic Relief Services - United States Conference of Catholic Bishops - CRS Nigeria. This program has the following goals: To reduce malaria burden to pre-elimination levels and bring malaria-related mortality to zero. The objectives of this program are: To ensure at least 80% of targeted population utilizes appropriate preventive measures by 2020. To test all care-seeking persons with suspected malaria using RDT or microscopy by 2020. To treat all individuals with confirmed malaria seen in private or public facilities with effective anti-malarial drug by 2020. To provide adequate information to all Nigerians such that at least 80% of the populace habitually takes appropriate malaria preventive and treatment measures as necessary by 2020. To ensure the timely availability of appropriate antimalarial medicines and commodities required for prevention and treatment of malaria in Nigeria wherever they are needed by 2018. At least 80% of health facilities in all LGAs report routinely on malaria by 2020. To strengthen governance and coordination of all stakeholders for effective program implementation towards an “A” rating by 2018 on a standardized scorecard

title.narrative: Impact indicator for NGA-M-CRS
Reported malaria cases (presumed and confirmed)
Malaria parasite prevalence: Proportion of children aged 6-59 months with malaria infection
Confirmed malaria cases (microscopy or RDT): rate per 1000 persons per year
All-cause under-5 mortality rate per 1000 live births
Inpatient malaria deaths per year: rate per 100,000 persons per year
Malaria test positivity rate
Modelled lives saved (based on latest epidemiological data)
Coverage / Output indicator for NGA-M-CRS
Number of long-lasting insecticidal nets distributed to at-risk populations through mass campaigns
Proportion of pregnant women attending antenatal clinics who received three or more doses of intermittent preventive treatment for malaria
Proportion of confirmed malaria cases that received first-line antimalarial treatment in the community
Number of long-lasting insecticidal nets distributed to targeted risk groups through continuous distribution
Percentage of HMIS or other routine reporting units submitting timely reports according to national guidelines
Proportion of confirmed malaria cases that received first-line antimalarial treatment at public sector health facilities
Percentage of children aged 3–59 months who received the full number of courses of SMC (3 or 4) per transmission season in the targeted areas
CM Other-1: Percentage of patients admitted for severe malaria that received injectable artesunate as treatment - public sector
Proportion of suspected malaria cases that receive a parasitological test at public sector health facilities
Proportion of suspected malaria cases that receive a parasitological test in the community
Proportion of health facilities without stock-outs of key commodities during the reporting period
PSM Other-1: Proportion of Health Facilities with no stock outs of tracer health product (AL1, AL4 and RDTs) lasting more than 7 days in the last bi-monthly reporting period
Proportion of malaria cases (presumed and confirmed) that received first line antimalarial treatment at public sector health facilities
Timeliness of facility reporting: Percentage of submitted facility monthly reports (for the reporting period) that are received on time per the national guidelines
Outcome indicator for NGA-M-CRS
Proportion of population that slept under an insecticide-treated net the previous night
Proportion of population using an insecticide-treated net among those with access to an insecticide-treated net
Proportion of households with at least one insecticide-treated net for every two people
Malaria O-other 3: Percent of children under 5 years of age with fever in the last 2 weeks who received any antimalarial treatment
Proportion of children under five years old who slept under an insecticide-treated net the previous night
Proportion of pregnant women who slept under an insecticide-treated net the previous night
Malaria O-other 2: Percent of children with fever in the last two weeks who had blood taken from a finger or heel for testing
Malaria O-other 1: Percent of pregnant women who received 3 or more doses of intermittent preventive treatment during antenatal care visits (in public & private facilities)
Proportion of population with access to an ITN within their household
